<tree mode="full" root="false" taxon="Reference"><frontmatter><trail/> <anchor>24244</anchor> <addr>sterling-2022-wits</addr>  <route>sterling-2022-wits.xml</route> <date>January 22, 2022</date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Make three to throw away: frontiers in homotopical proof assistants</title> <meta name="slides">https://www.jonmsterling.com/slides/sterling-2022-wits.pdf</meta><meta name="video">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lqBFq7aRReY</meta><meta name="venue">Workshop on the Implementation of Type Systems (keynote)</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For six years, I have served as the founder and technical leader of the RedPRL Development Team which has produced three interactive proof assistants for variants of cubical type theory: RedPRL, redtt, and cooltt. I will share several lessons that we have learned about the design and implementation of homotopical proof assistants along this journey. This talk discusses joint work with <link href="carloangiuli.xml" type="local">Carlo Angiuli</link>, Evan Cavallo, <link href="favonia.xml" type="local">Favonia</link>, and Reed Mullanix.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree mode="full" root="false" taxon="Person"><frontmatter><trail/> <anchor>24246</anchor> <addr>carloangiuli</addr>  <route>carloangiuli.xml</route>   <title>Carlo Angiuli</title> <meta name="external">https://carloangiuli.com/</meta><meta name="phd-advisor">robertharper</meta><meta name="institution">Indiana University</meta><meta name="position">Assistant Professor</meta><meta name="postdoc-advisor">robertharper</meta><meta name="orcid">0000-0002-9590-3303</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree><tree mode="full" root="false" taxon="Person"><frontmatter><trail/> <anchor>24248</anchor> <addr>favonia</addr>  <route>favonia.xml</route>   <title>Kuen-Bang Hou (Favonia)</title> <meta name="external">https://www.favonia.org/</meta><meta name="institution">University of Minnesota</meta><meta name="position">Assistant Professor</meta><meta name="phd-advisor">robertharper</meta><meta name="orcid">0000-0002-2310-3673</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>